 Terminating a C program is very simple. In C, the main function is the entry point of your C program. You can terminate a C program by calling the `exit` function. The exit function terminates the C program. Here is a simple example of terminating a C program:

```c
#include <stdio.h>

int main() {
    printf("Hello, World!\n");

    // Call the exit function
    exit(0);

    return 0;
}
```

When you run this program, it will print "Hello, World!" to the console. Then, it calls the `exit` function, which terminates the C program.

